oakcurric:unit-3087
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Non-examined assessment: netball practical"@en ;
  curric:slug "non-examined-assessment-netball-practical" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit provides pupils with the knowledge and opportunity to replicate skills
  in isolation and in performance scenarios in netball. As a popular team sport offered by
  many pupils it will cover passing/ receiving, footwork, dodging, shooting, marking,
  intercepting and decision making."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know the correct technique and relevant rules for
  netball from key stage 3 PE. This unit builds upon this by providing the opportunity to
  evaluate technique and practise some observation and analysis skills. Positioned during the
  spring term of year 10, it will encourage engagement in extracurricular opportunities,
  including local clubs and competitions, which will allow further improvement of performance.
  This unit will help to prepare students for the practical GCSE moderation in Year 11.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3087-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3087-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3087-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3087-4 ;
  curric:id "3087"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.832130Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-rules-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-3096
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Socio-cultural influences: engagement patterns"@en ;
  curric:slug "socio-cultural-influences-engagement-patterns" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will examine the socio-cultural factors that impact on physical
  activity, sport and society. Understanding engagement patterns of different social groups
  and factors affecting participation require an ability to interpret and analyse data."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know that some sports and physical activities have
  lower representation from certain socio-economic backgrounds and that it is important we
  break down these barriers to participation. This unit cements that knowledge from key stage
  3, engagement in sport in the local community and awareness of press coverage relating to
  different social groups. Later in socio-cultural influences pupils will study
  commercialisation, ethics and behaviour and make connections between the media, sportspeople,
  sponsors, spectators and society at large.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3096-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3096-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3096-3 ;
  curric:id "3096"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.916823Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-connect-cultural-and-ethical-awareness .

oakcurric:unit-3258
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Physical training: methods of training"@en ;
  curric:slug "physical-training-methods-of-training" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will describe and enable pupils to experience different types of
  training before analysing which ones are most suited to different types of sporting
  performers."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will continue to develop their understanding of different ways to
  train for improved everyday health and/ or sporting performance. From the earlier physical
  training units pupils will understand the components of fitness that should be prioritised
  for different sports and/ or playing positions to inform which types of training are most
  relevant and beneficial. Later in physical training they will consider injuries and injury
  prevention as well as performance enhancing drugs.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3258-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3258-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3258-3 ;
  curric:id "3258"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.960571Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living .

oakcurric:unit-3080
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Physical training: principles of training"@en ;
  curric:slug "physical-training-principles-of-training" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will explore the guidelines or principles that we should follow when
  training to improve health, fitness and sporting performance."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will continue to develop their understanding of how to train for
  improved everyday health and/ or sporting performance. From the applied anatomy and
  physiology units they will have an in-depth understanding of how our bodies respond to
  exercise and adapt to cope better after a period of training and this knowledge lays the
  foundations for understanding these training principles. Later in physical training they will
  discover different methods of training that are of benefit to different individuals at
  different times in their training programmes.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3080-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3080-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3080-3 ;
  curric:id "3080"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.063337Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living .

oakcurric:unit-3079
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Physical training: health and fitness"@en ;
  curric:slug "physical-training-health-and-fitness" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will explore the relationship between health, fitness, exercise and
  performance before unpacking the different components of fitness. This understanding will
  include key definitions, how to test and train each but also which components are most
  important for different sports."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have a basic appreciation of how fitness comprises
  different elements that are important to a greater or lesser extent depending on the
  activity. From the applied anatomy and physiology units they will also have an in-depth
  understanding of how our bodies respond to exercise and adapt to cope better after a period
  of training. Later in physical training they will explore principles and methods of training
  as well as how to reduce the risk of injury through overtraining or poor programming.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3079-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3079-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3079-3 ;
  curric:id "3079"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.069990Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living .

oakcurric:unit-3861
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Remote learning: moving with athleticism"@en ;
  curric:slug "home-learning-moving-with-athleticism" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will support the development of complex and demanding movement
  combinations with a focus on purpose, precision and power. Pupils will accurately
  replicate complex movement combinations and reflect on their performance before refining
  and repeating."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have developed their confidence moving with agility,
  balance, core stability, body tension and coordination. Pupils will plan and experiment with
  complex movement sequences. Pupils will have the chance to further develop their reflective
  and analytical skills.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3861-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3861-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3861-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3861-4 ;
  curric:id "3861"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.128173Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3862
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Remote learning: advanced dance"@en ;
  curric:slug "home-learning-advanced-dance" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit uses a thematic approach with body language and improvisation to express
  emotions and feelings. Pupils develop movement ideas beyond those introduced. Open-ended
  tasks encourage varied responses, building creative thinking and expressive skills."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit offers scope for pupils to draw upon prior learning and combine
  performative, choreographic and stylistic features to produce a range of effects and be able
  to accurately identify the strengths and weaknesses in their own work. Pupils will be able to
  make recommendations for improvement.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3862-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3862-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3862-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3862-4 ;
  curric:id "3862"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.133307Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3863
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Remote learning: outdoor adventure activities and problem solving"@en ;
  curric:slug "home-learning-outdoor-adventure-activities-and-problem-solving" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores pupils' ability to use a map, compass and plan a route.
  Developing the confidence to plan and follow movement routes accurately is a valuable
  cross curricular skill."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have developed basic skills to operate within and as a
  team, but this unit challenges pupils to apply them in unique scenarios that require problem
  solving and creative thinking. Later in outdoor adventurous activities, pupils will get the
  opportunity to engage in activities beyond the school walls which will further develop their
  teamwork and leadership skills.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3863-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3863-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3863-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3863-4 ;
  curric:id "3863"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.155974Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3074
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Anatomy and physiology: the musculoskeletal system"@en ;
  curric:slug "anatomy-and-physiology-the-musculoskeletal-system" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will examine the structure and function of both the skeletal and the
  muscular systems. It includes locating major bones and muscles before defining and
  analysing what movements are possible at different joints."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Key stage 3 PE and biology will have introduced pupils to some major bones
  and muscles. This unit cements this knowledge through the application of complex anatomical
  and physiological terminology. This forms the foundation of future sports science study and
  supports a deeper understanding of the impact of the musculoskeletal system on health,
  fitness and sporting performance. Later anatomy and physiology units will develop knowledge
  from this unit in the examination of other body systems, such as, the cardiovascular system
  and their application within movement analysis.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3074-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3074-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3074-3 ;
  curric:id "3074"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.158939Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living .

oakcurric:unit-3095
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Sport psychology: goal setting, guidance and feedback"@en ;
  curric:slug "sport-psychology-goal-setting-guidance-and-feedback" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops understanding of how goal setting and SMART targets can be used
  effectively to improve performance as well as unpicking the different types of guidance
  and feedback that help us learn sporting skills."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know what skillful performance looks like and ways to
  improve physiological performance by applying principles and methods of training but this
  unit extends basic awareness of psychological factors that can also have a huge impact on
  motivation to train, progress, and end results. Later in sport psychology pupils will learn
  how mental preparation can aid performance further.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3095-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3095-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3095-3 ;
  curric:id "3095"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.192238Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-decision-making-problem-solving-and-creative-thinking .

oakcurric:unit-3094
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Sport psychology: skill and ability"@en ;
  curric:slug "sport-psychology-skill-and-ability" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops understanding of what skillful movement looks like and how it
  can be classified on different continua. It builds on the basic understanding that
  psychological factors can affect sporting performance in the same way physiological
  factors influence it."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know that psychological factors connected with our
  brain can have an equally significant impact on performance as physiological factors relating
  to body systems that have been explored in previous units. This unit builds on that basic
  appreciation from key stage 3 PE and will ignite an interest in this growing area of sports
  science study. Later in sport psychology pupils will explore how to make best use of goal
  setting, guidance, feedback and mental preparation.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3094-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3094-2 ;
  curric:id "3094"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.206445Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-decision-making-problem-solving-and-creative-thinking .

oakcurric:unit-3051
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and wellbeing: commitment to a personalised training plan"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-wellbeing-commitment-to-a-personalised-training-plan" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ ability to design and carry out a training
  programme with a focus on physical fitness and commitment to exercise that is enjoyable
  and tailored. Pupils will also learn about nutrition to help support them in living a
  healthy and active life beyond school."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have deepened their understanding of how to set SMART
  targets that support a meaningful and motivating fitness programme. They will have learnt
  about some of the barriers to participation and how they can be overcome along with the long
  term health and fitness benefits of both continuous and interval training programmes to
  include circuits. Later in health and wellbeing pupils will explore a variety of additional
  approaches to holistic wellbeing to include couch to 5k; yoga, pilates and mindfulness; and
  exercises associated with martial arts and self-defence.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3051-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3051-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3051-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3051-4 ;
  curric:id "3051"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.281813Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-engagement-and-enjoyment .

oakcurric:unit-3864
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Remote learning: health, fitness and wellbeing"@en ;
  curric:slug "home-learning-health-fitness-and-wellbeing" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ ability to design and carry out a training
  programme with a focus on physical fitness and commitment to exercise that is enjoyable
  and tailored. Pupils will also learn about nutrition to help support them in living a
  healthy and active life beyond school."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will have already enhanced their understanding of how to set SMART
  targets that support a meaningful and motivating fitness programme. They will have learnt
  about some of the benefits and types of training programmes available to them.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3864-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3864-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3864-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3864-4 ;
  curric:id "3864"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.309430Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3101
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Exam technique and answering the extended answer questions"@en ;
  curric:slug "exam-technique-and-answering-the-extended-answer-questions" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will explore how best to achieve top marks in the examination with a
  particular focus on the extended answer questions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know all of the content required in the examination
  and this unit will enable them to learn about and practice tackling the longer mark
  questions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3101-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3101-2 ;
  curric:id "3101"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.376643Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-evaluation-analysis-and-reflection ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-cultural-and-ethical-awareness .

oakcurric:unit-3860
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Remote learning: designing competitive games"@en ;
  curric:slug "home-learning-designing-competitive-games" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit offers opportunities to design games requiring ball control and tactical
  skill to achieve personal bests in complex tasks. Pupils will think creatively to adapt
  games to their environment and equipment, while challenging others to reach their own
  personal bests."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have explored a variety of ways to control a ball
  using their hands, feet and other body parts. This unit takes that understanding into a
  variety of game situations that require focus and an awareness of their environment to modify
  accordingly. Pupils will also learn about how to compete with themself and others.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3860-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3860-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3860-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3860-4 ;
  curric:id "3860"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.383252Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3100
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and well-being: diet and nutrition"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-well-being-diet-and-nutrition" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will examine how much energy is needed to function and the additional
  requirements of a balanced diet, good hydration and potential tweaks to food consumption
  to allow for optimal sporting performance and energy balance."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know about the relationship between exercise and diet
  on weight loss or gain. This unit deepens this understanding with a specific focus on
  nutrition and the importance of avoiding malnutrition. This final unit draws together a lot
  of what pupils have learnt about body systems, physical training, sporting performance and
  more general health and well-being to promote active lifestyle choices or post-16 study to
  learn more.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3100-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3100-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3100-3 ;
  curric:id "3100"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.410956Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living .

oakcurric:unit-3098
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Socio-cultural influences: ethics and behaviour"@en ;
  curric:slug "socio-cultural-influences-ethics-and-behaviour" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will examine socio-cultural factors concerned with sportsmanship,
  gamesmanship and deviance in sport to understand the choices made by some sportspeople and
  spectators."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know how engagement patterns vary based on
  socio-economic group and the important role the media and sponsorship can play in promoting
  sport for all. This unit reinforces that knowledge from the preceding units and delves deeper
  into ethical behaviours. Links from this can be made into reasons for participation in the
  following health and well-being unit.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3098-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3098-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3098-3 ;
  curric:id "3098"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.525388Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-connect-cultural-and-ethical-awareness .

oakcurric:unit-3558
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Sports psychology: mental preparation for performance"@en ;
  curric:slug "sports-psychology-mental-preparation-for-performance" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops understanding of how to best prepare our mind for competition
  and explores strategies like mental rehearsal, visualisation and imagery to support peak
  performance."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know that part of warming up for competition is about
  getting in the right psychological state for optimum performance. This unit builds on that
  basic understanding from key stage 3, exposure to sports participation and following elite
  sport in the media. Later pupils will move on to learn about the various socio-cultural
  influences on participation and performance.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3558-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3558-2 ;
  curric:id "3558"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.584414Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-decision-making-problem-solving-and-creative-thinking .

oakcurric:unit-3088
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Non-examined assessment: rugby league practical"@en ;
  curric:slug "non-examined-assessment-rugby-practical" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit provides pupils with the knowledge and opportunity to replicate skills
  in isolation and in performance scenarios in rugby. As a popular team sport offered by
  many pupils it will cover passing/ receiving, ball handling, tackling, rucking, scrums,
  line outs, kicking and decision making."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know the basics of play and relevant rules for rugby
  from key stage 3 PE. This unit builds upon this by providing the opportunity to evaluate
  technique and practise some observation and analysis skills. Positioned during the autumn
  term of year 10, it will encourage engagement in extracurricular opportunities, including
  local clubs and competitions, which will allow further improvement of performance. This unit
  will help to prepare students for the practical GCSE moderation in Year 11.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3088-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3088-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3088-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3088-4 ;
  curric:id "3088"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.652134Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-rules-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-3089
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Non-examined assessment: badminton practical"@en ;
  curric:slug "non-examined-assessment-badminton-practical" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit provides pupils with the knowledge and opportunity to replicate skills
  in isolation and in performance scenarios in badminton. As a popular individual and team
  sport offered by many pupils it will cover serving, footwork, forehand and backhand shot
  selection, as well as competition rules."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know the correct technique and relevant rules for
  badminton from key stage 3 PE. This unit builds upon this by providing the opportunity to
  evaluate technique and practise some observation and analysis skills. Positioned during the
  spring term of year 10, it will encourage engagement in extracurricular opportunities,
  including local clubs and competitions, which will allow further improvement of performance.
  This unit will help to prepare students for the practical GCSE moderation in Year 11.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3089-1 ,
