oakcurric:unit-3067
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Net and wall games: teaching others tactics and strategies in table tennis"@en ;
  curric:slug "net-and-wall-games-teaching-others-tactics-and-strategies-in-table-tennis" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop core skills required for table tennis and transfer ideas,
  tactics and strategies from other racket sports. Pupils will focus on fair play and learn
  about a variety of ways to organise tournaments to help balance competition."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have sharpened their team working skills and ability
  to manage conflict in different situations. Learning how to organise tournaments and support
  each other to perform at their best will help cement prior learning in a new context. Pupils
  can take these skills, experiences and positive attitudes towards participation in a range of
  net and wall games into life with confidence and consequently lead healthy, active lives
  beyond school. They will also be able to spectate and socialise in and around competitive
  sport with an appreciation and understanding of how to play.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3067-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3067-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3067-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3067-4 ;
  curric:id "3067"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.819700Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-3063
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games: tactics and strategies when leading a team in Korfball"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-tactics-and-strategies-when-leading-a-team-in-korfball" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit challenges pupils to apply some tactics and strategies gained from
  netball and basketball to a new sport whilst focusing on respect for others and leadership
  skill development. Pupils will apply more advanced tactics and strategies whilst securing
  their understanding of a new game."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have developed a wide variety of skills, tactics and
  strategies from various games with the ball in hand. This unit requires pupils to lead and
  coach each other in a different game. Pupils can take these skills, experiences and positive
  attitudes towards participation in a range of invasion games into life with confidence and
  consequently lead healthy, active lives beyond school. They will also be able to spectate and
  socialise in and around competitive sport with an appreciation and understanding of how to
  play.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3063-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3063-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3063-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3063-4 ;
  curric:id "3063"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.821911Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
