    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-rules-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-3779
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Kin-ball: communicating and solving problems through an inclusive game"@en ;
  curric:slug "kin-ball-communicating-and-solving-problems-through-an-inclusive-game" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores a variety of tactics and strategies that can be transferred
  from other team games to kin-ball. Pupils will be challenged to demonstrate and develop
  their problem solving and communication skills in this unique and inclusive game with
  three teams."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have developed ways to adapt skills, tactics and
  strategies from various forms of handball, netball and basketball but this unit requires
  pupils to learn and problem solve in a different game. This unit provides an opportunity to
  also learn about how positional play needs to be adapted to a unique game with three teams on
  the court at any one time. Later in invasion games they will apply more advanced tactics and
  strategies.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3779-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3779-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3779-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3779-4 ;
  curric:id "3779"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.955860Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3099
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and well-being: reasons for participation"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-well-being-reasons-for-participation" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will examine the benefits of participating in physical activity and
  sport on health, fitness and well-being to include physical, emotional/ mental and social
  factors. It will also explore the consequences of a sedentary lifestyle and implications
  of ill health."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know about components of fitness and the long term
  benefits of training on their body systems from the physical training and anatomy and
  physiology units. This unit connects the physiological and psychological factors with a focus
  on everyday health and well-being. Later in health, fitness and well-being pupils will study
  how diet and nutrition also contribute to well-being.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3099-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3099-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3099-3 ;
  curric:id "3099"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.958398Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living .

oakcurric:unit-3774
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Non-examined assessment: handball practical"@en ;
  curric:slug "non-examined-assessment-handball-practical" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit provides pupils with the knowledge and opportunity to replicate skills
  in isolation and in performance scenarios in handball. As a team sport participated in by
  many pupils it will cover passing/ receiving, ball handling, dribbling, shooting,
  blocking, screening and decision making."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know the basics of play and relevant rules for
  handball from Key Stage 3 PE. This unit builds upon this by providing the opportunity to
  evaluate technique and practise some observation and analysis skills. Positioned during year
  10, it will encourage engagement in extracurricular opportunities, including local clubs and
  competitions, which will allow further improvement of performance. This unit will help to
  prepare students for the practical GCSE moderation in Year 11.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3774-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3774-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3774-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3774-4 ;
  curric:id "3774"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.961578Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3062
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games: problem solving with tactics and strategies through T1 rugby"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-problem-solving-with-tactics-and-strategies-through-rugby" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit challenges pupils to problem solve and make good decisions under
  pressure in T1 rugby games and scenarios. Pupils will apply more advanced tactics and
  strategies whilst securing their understanding of the nuances in the laws of the game."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have developed a variety of skills, tactics and
  strategies from various games with the ball in hand, at feet and in rugby and other invasion
  game situations (such as Kabaddi), but this unit requires pupils to learn how to problem
  solve in a different version of the game. Later in invasion games they will apply more
  advanced tactics and strategies to other new games.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3062-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3062-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3062-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3062-4 ;
  curric:id "3062"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.981395Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-decision-making-problem-solving-and-creative-thinking ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas .

oakcurric:unit-3061
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and wellbeing: HIIT and couch to 5k team challenges to develop fitness"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-wellbeing-hiit-and-couch-to-5k-team-challenges-to-develop-fitness" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ understanding of the principles of training through
  a running programme that stretches them as an individual but also their contribution to a
  team. Their cardiovascular endurance will improve whilst taking responsibility for their
  own training."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have designed their own training programme to work on
  aspects of physical fitness that matter to them. This unit challenges them to work together
  towards common goals of improved cardiovascular endurance and the power of taking
  responsibility for following a prescribed programme based on current fitness levels. Later in
  health and wellbeing pupils will explore approaches to holistic wellbeing to include yoga,
  pilates and mindfulness; and exercises associated with martial arts and self-defence.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3061-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3061-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3061-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3061-4 ;
  curric:id "3061"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.983630Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living .

oakcurric:unit-3068
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Target games: experience lifestyle games like golf and kubb"@en ;
  curric:slug "target-games-experience-lifestyle-games-like-golf-and-kubb" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ awareness of and ability to seek joy in lifestyle
  target games they can access in the community. Pupils will be supported to manage their
  emotions and apply mental preparation to closed skills to maximise performance."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have developed an appreciation of some of the target
  and garden games that promote social connection and potential catharsis from everyday life.
  They will have learnt simple ways to manage their emotions but this unit enables a deeper
  look into psychological approaches that help find a state of flow. Pupils can take these
  skills, experiences and positive attitudes towards participation into life with confidence
  and consequently seek fun ways to lead healthy, active lives beyond school.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3068-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3068-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3068-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3068-4 ;
  curric:id "3068"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.105477Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-3060
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Striking and fielding games: teaching others to play creative cricket games"@en ;
  curric:slug "striking-and-fielding-games-teaching-others-to-play-creative-cricket-games" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ ability to teach each other and to play a variety
  of creative cricket games independently. Pupils will draw on their leadership skills to
  train, compete and perform."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have improved their consistency, timing and fluency in
  the execution of batting, bowling and fielding skills. They will design games that enable
  groups to become immersed in activity which will have a positive effect on mental health.
  Later in striking and fielding games pupils will be challenged to adapt and transfer skills
  to softball whilst learning a new set of rules, techniques and tactics. They will also be
  able to spectate and socialise in and around competitive sport with an appreciation and
  understanding of how to play.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3060-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3060-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3060-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3060-4 ;
  curric:id "3060"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.107828Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-3070
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Net and wall games: tactics and strategies in volleyball"@en ;
  curric:slug "net-and-wall-games-tactics-and-strategies-in-volleyball" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will build core skills and develop the use of game tactics to outwit
  opponents in pressurised situations. Pupils will sharpen their team working skills with a
  focus on managing conflict and generating the conditions for a great game regardless of
  the skill level of the participants."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have shown commitment and an ability to transfer
  skills between different racket sports and now they will be tasked to apply tactics and
  strategies in a larger team sport. They will have had experience officiating and analysing
  performance which can now be applied to volleyball. Later in net and wall games they will
  learn to apply key principles in table tennis and feel ready to approach any net and wall
  game with confidence.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3070-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3070-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3070-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3070-4 ;
  curric:id "3070"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.190493Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-3058
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Striking and fielding games: evaluate and improve performance in softball"@en ;
  curric:slug "striking-and-fielding-games-evaluate-and-improve-performance-in-softball" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop batting, pitching and fielding skills unique to softball,
  such as using a glove and applying the rules around strikes and base running. Pupils will
  be challenged to evaluate both their own performance and that of others as they apply
  tenacity to this American game."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have explored rules, techniques and tactics for
  batting, bowling and fielding in rounders and cricket. Previous statistical and performance
  analysis skills will help with decision making. Pupils can take these skills, experiences and
  positive attitudes towards participation in a range of striking and fielding games into life
  with confidence and consequently lead healthy, active lives beyond school. They will also be
  able to spectate and socialise in and around competitive sport with an appreciation and
  understanding of how to play.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3058-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3058-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3058-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3058-4 ;
  curric:id "3058"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.192404Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-evaluation-analysis-and-reflection ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-3780
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Non-examined assessment: rugby union practical"@en ;
  curric:slug "non-examined-assessment-rugby-union-practical" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit provides pupils with the knowledge and opportunity to replicate skills
  in isolation and in performance scenarios in rugby. As a popular team sport offered by
  many pupils it will cover passing/ receiving, ball handling, tackling, rucking, scrums,
  line outs, kicking and decision making."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know the basics of play and relevant rules for rugby
  from key stage 3 PE. This unit builds upon this by providing the opportunity to evaluate
  technique and practise some observation and analysis skills. Positioned during the autumn
  term of year 10, it will encourage engagement in extracurricular opportunities, including
  local clubs and competitions, which will allow further improvement of performance. This unit
  will help to prepare students for the practical GCSE moderation in Year 11.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3780-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3780-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3780-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3780-4 ;
  curric:id "3780"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.195037Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3059
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Outdoor adventurous activities: outdoor pursuits and team challenges"@en ;
  curric:slug "outdoor-adventurous-activities-outdoor-and-athletic-pursuits" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ independence and team working skills through
  outdoor pursuits and challenges. It will challenge pupils to think about and gain
  competence in lifestyle pursuits that encourage engagement beyond school whilst also
  developing physical fitness and connection to nature."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have found their struggle zone with regard to
  continuous running and explosive power tasks as well as facing physical and intellectual
  challenges. They will have learnt about fitness components, training methods and target
  setting but now get to channel this knowledge into more authentic environments and learn more
  about completing challenges in small groups. Pupils can take these skills, experiences and
  positive attitudes towards participation into life with confidence and consequently lead
  healthy, active lives beyond school.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3059-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3059-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3059-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3059-4 ;
  curric:id "3059"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.200741Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-cultural-and-ethical-awareness .

oakcurric:unit-3064
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and wellbeing: yoga, pilates and mindfulness for life"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-wellbeing-yoga-pilates-and-mindfulness-for-life" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ awareness of the restorative powers of pilates,
  mindfulness and other daily routines that can support holistic wellbeing and help with
  stress management. Pupils will experience a variety of classes and also learn about the
  power of breathwork."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have experienced a wide range of moderate to vigorous
  activity based fitness. This unit takes an alternative approach by considering ways to calm
  the mind and body but also to improve flexibility and holistic health. They will have already
  learnt about principles of training and this unit requires maturity and an open mind to make
  the most of it. Later in health and wellbeing pupils will explore exercises associated with
  martial arts and self-defence as they continue to discover, fine tune and commit to lifelong
  fitness habits.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3064-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3064-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3064-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3064-4 ;
  curric:id "3064"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.298160Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-engagement-and-enjoyment .

oakcurric:unit-3065
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and wellbeing: martial arts and self-defence"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-wellbeing-martial-arts-and-self-defence" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ movement competence through a variety of kata along
  with their emotional and spiritual development as they experience self-improvement
  challenges associated with martial arts and self-defence practice. Pupils will also
  develop their metacognition and courage."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have experienced a broad range of classes and fitness
  regimes that are widely available and popular in the local community and/ or at home. They
  will have learnt about physiological, psychological and socio-cultural factors connected with
  participation. Pupils can take these skills, experiences and positive attitudes towards
  participation into life with confidence and consequently lead healthy, active lives beyond
  school.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3065-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3065-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3065-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3065-4 ;
