oakcurric:unit-3057
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Invasion games: tactics and strategies in tchoukball"@en ;
  curric:slug "invasion-games-tactics-and-strategies-in-tchoukball" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores a variety of tactics and strategies that can be transferred
  from other team games to tchoukball. Pupils will be challenged to demonstrate and develop
  their integrity by showing good moral principles playing without an official."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have developed ways to adapt skills, tactics and
  strategies from various forms of handball, netball and basketball but this unit requires
  pupils to learn and problem solve in a different game. This unit provides an opportunity to
  also learn about forces and laws of motion in action in sport. Later in invasion games they
  will apply more advanced tactics and strategies.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3057-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3057-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3057-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3057-4 ;
