  defenders."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.341699Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29125-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: to dribble the ball and advance into space requires determination and
  effort."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.341703Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-29125-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: receiving and moving with the ball requires an awareness of where your team
  are on court."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.341707Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23088-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Media types include television, radio, the press, the internet and social media."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.343086Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23088-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Media can enhance performers' visibility, provide sponsorship opportunities and a
  platform for promotional activities."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.343090Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23088-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Media coverage can lead to increased pressure, loss of privacy and negative public
  scrutiny."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.343094Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23088-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Media coverage boosts a sport's popularity and finances but can also lead to a focus
  on entertainment over competition."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.343098Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23088-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Media can increase sponsor visibility and engagement but may create scrutiny or
  controversy for officials and sponsors."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.343102Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22932-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
