  fluidly between poses."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.344533Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22932-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Move: with each pose, engage all muscles particularly at the core, allowing for
  increased stability."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.344537Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22932-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Think: focusing on the breath can calm the mind and reduce mental chatter to improve
  mindfulness skills."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.344541Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22932-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Feel: being comfortable and calm promotes relaxation, leading to smoother and more
  fluid movement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.344545Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22932-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Connect: fostering mindfulness and well-being, while encouraging group rhythm,
  creates a strong sense of community."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.344549Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-22952-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
